document_data.Currency:
Certain underwater races used pearls as currency rather than coins. The value of this currency changed according to several factors: the size of the pearl, measured from a standard of {{SI|0.25|in|m|long=yes}}; its rarity; and quality. In the [[Sea of Fallen Stars]], the value of a pearl was determined primarily by its color:

* white pearl, or "seyar": 1 cp undersea and 2 sp ashore;
* yellow pearl, or "hayar": 1 sp undersea and 2 gp ashore;
* green pearl, or "tayar": 1 gp undersea and 20 gp on land;
* blue pearl, or "nuyar": 5 gp undersea and 100 gp on land;
* olive pearl, or "olmar", {{SI|7|in|c|long=yes}} long, {{SI|3|in|c|long=yes}} wide, and diamond-shaped: 500 gp undersea and over 2,000 gp ashore.

Notable Users of Pearls.Religions:
* Pearls were considered sacred by followers of [[Deep Sashelas]] and [[Dugmaren Brightmantle]]&mdash;appropriate for sacrifice, or to be consecrated for use, or recognized as boons or omens when found.{{Cite web enhancement/Deity Do's and Don'ts|11}}
* White pearls were sacred to followers of [[Savras]].{{Cite web enhancement/Deity Do's and Don'ts|13}}
* Black pearls were sacred to followers of [[Shargaas]]{{Cite web enhancement/Deity Do's and Don'ts|14}} and [[Vhaeraun]].{{Cite web enhancement/Deity Do's and Don'ts|15}}
* The temple complexes of [[Blibdoolpoolp]] typically had large black pearls in them. Changes in their coloration were seen as favorable omens.
